recitals:
,
Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community,
Having regard to Council Regulation (EEC) No 822/87 of 16 March 1987 on the common organization of the market in wine (1), as last amended by Regulation (EEC) No 1566/93 (2), and in particular Article 46 (5) and 81 thereof,
Having regard to Council Regulation (EEC) No 3813/92 of 28 December 1992 on the unit of account and the conversion rates to be applied for the purposes of the common agricultural policy (3), as last amended by Regulation (EC) No 3528/93 (4),
Whereas Article 1 (2) of Commission Regulation (EEC) No 3461/85 of 9 December 1985 on the organization of campaigns to promote the consumption of grape juice (5), as last amended by Regulation (EEC) No 1977/93 (6), provides that the Member States in  which the campaigns to promote the consumption of grape juice are to be carried out and the total amounts allocated for the financing of the campaigns in each of the said Member States must be determined for each wine year;
Whereas Article 4 (2) of Commission Regulation (EEC) No 2641/88 of 25 August 1988 laying down detailed rules for the application of the aid scheme for the use of grapes, grape must and concentrated grape must to produce grape juice (7), as last amended  by Regulation (EEC) No 2056/91 (8), fixes that part of the aid intended to finance 35 % of the promotion campaign;
Whereas Annex IV to Commission Regulation (EEC) No 2093/93 of 28 July 1993 fixing the buying-in prices, aids and certain other amounts applicable for the 1993/94 wine year to intervention measures in the wine sector (9), fixes the amount of aid for the  1993/94 wine year;
Whereas the amount available for such financing depends on the quantities of the products in respect of which the aid is to be granted; whereas the estimate adopted for the 1985/86, 1986/87, 1987/88, 1988/89, 1989/90, 1990/91, 1991/92 and 1992/93  campaigns will make it possible to finance these campaigns; whereas the amount available for financing the measure for 1993/94 is estimated at ECU 7 200 000;
Whereas the amount adopted is not sufficient to enable effective campaigns to be mounted throughout the Community; whereas it therefore appears advisable to continue to operate promotional schemes in those Member States where campaigns have been mounted  in previous years; whereas, however, an amount of ECU 1 600 000 is reserved for Italy pending demonstration by that Member State after completion of the 1992/93 campaign currently being implemented, that the action taken has produced positive and  qualifiable effects on the consumption of grape juice;
Whereas, in order to ensure better management of the budget funds, a final date must be fixed for the signing and payment of contracts;
Whereas the measures provided for in this Regulation are in accordance with the opinion of the Management Committee for Wine,
